  "title": "Data Analyst",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:<br />1. Develop comprehensive product metrics and quantitative measurement structure based on product stages and business purposes;<br />2. Prototype analysis pipelines to provide insights, and provide quick responses to business inquiries and events;<br />3. Conduct routine and non-routine end-to-end analyses with large, complex data sets, and make recommendations on appropriate solutions;<br />4. Cooperate with PM / Ops team / R&D / Algo, promote the implementation of optimization scheme, and bring about the actual improvement and growth of the business.<br /><br />Qualifications</p><p>Minimum Qualifications:<br />1. Bachelor degree or above in Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics or other related majors;<br />2. Relevant working experience in Data Analysis, Data Science, or machine learning;<br />3. Proficient in SQL/Python or R, experienced in massive data manipulation, machine learning & modeling;<br />4. Solid technical & knowledge of A/B testing methodologies, can consistently explore and find the best practice;<br />5. Strong technical leadership combined with hands-on data mining and machine learning application experience;<br />6. Insightful data sense and rigorous logical mindset, capable of providing systematic approaches to solve business problems;<br />7. Quickly familiar with and starting a new business; Can lead a small project team to support business. Willingness to both teach others and learn new techniques.<br /><br />Preferred Qualifications:<br />1. 5 years and above relevant work experience from a large-scale internet business;<br />2.Background in internet companies or payments is preferred;<br />3.Strong interest in Data Analysis, Data Mining is preferred；</p>",
